The Capstone customer most likely would want to use a private repository as it will provide security for the project being made. As well as create accountability on users that has permissions. Having a proper encryption behind the project will ensure the safety of the project can never be jeopardize for the client. This will also keep the project from falling into open source and while open source allows possibly more enhancements it will have the negative effect of the client possibly losing rights to the application created.
